String Template In the past, we relied on string concatenation to format output for print statements. System.out.println(arr[i] + &quot; &quot; + &quot;From for loop&quot;);
Now this will change from Java 21 as String Template is here. String templates offer a more elegant approach by letting you embed expressions directly within the string. This improves readability and maintainability of your code.
What is String Template? String Template is a process of substituting values of variables into placeholders in a string.
